added.clinical_concept: Spontaneously healed rupture of right axillary aneurysm
added.rationale: Identification of a healed rupture suggests previous vessel wall compromise and risk for re-rupture, guiding surgical planning.

evidence.snippet_B: contour irregularities at the distal end of the right-side aneurysm. These latter findings were proposed to be due to a spontaneously healed rupture.
